File: A healthcare worker performing a COVID-19 test. AFP/Ina Fassbender JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department has reported 4,400 new COVID-19 cases, the highest daily increase since August. This brings the cumulative number of COVID-19 infections to over 800,000. READ: KZN cancels major parties, events as COVID-19 infections rise 94 more people have died, taking the death toll to over 21,803. More than 739,000 people have recovered. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs